    dc:creator "Avila, Luciano Javier; Perez, Cristian Hernan Fulvio; Minoli, Ignacio; Morando, Mariana" ;
    dc:date "2012" ;
    dc:title "A new species of Homonota (Reptilia: Squamata: Gekkota: Phyllodactylidae) from the Ventania mountain range, Southeastern Pampas, Buenos Aires Province, Argentina" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282040>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282041>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282038>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282044>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282042>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282043>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282045>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282046> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282040>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Homonota williamsii sp. nov., adult from Sierra de la Ventana, Tornquist Department, Buenos Aires province, Argentina. (not the holotype)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/282040/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282041>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Homonota williamsii sp. nov., holotype adult male in dorsal and ventral view (MLP. S 2630), from Sierra de la Ventana, Tornquist Department, Buenos Aires province, Argentina." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/282041/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282038>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Species of Homonota from Argentina: (A) Homonota underwoodi, (B) H. whitii, (C) H. fasciata, (D) H. andicola, (E) H. borellii, (F) H. darwinii." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/282038/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282044>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Meatus auditory on: (A) Homonota williamsii sp. nov. (MLP. S 2630), large, oval, oblique and serrated; (B) H. borellii (LJAMM-CNP 14378), round, small and not serrated." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/282044/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282042>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Midbody dorsal scales of: (A) Homonota williamsii sp. nov. (MLP. S 2630), moderately keeled series along the dorsum; (B) H. darwinii (LJAMM-CNP 9789), smooth scales series." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/282042/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282043>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Subcaudal scales of: (A) Homonota williamsii sp. nov. (MLP. S 2630), enlarged, rounded and rectangular longitudinally elongated; (B) H. borellii (LJAMM-CNP 14378), enlarged, elongated and transversely rectangular; (C) H. darwinii (LJAMM-CNP 9789), enlarged, rhombic and scalloped." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/282043/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282045>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Map of southern Buenos Aires region showing the complex landscape of the Ventania mountain range. The black circle marks the Homonota williamsii sp. nov. type locality and white circles paratype localities. Main mountain ranges, rivers, and roads are marked. Gray circles: cities. Inset: Region in South America." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/282045/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282046>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Type locality of Homonota williamsii sp. nov.. Above: general view of the area. Below: close view of the common outcrops where lizards were collected." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/282046/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

